Strong
Why HMAC-SHA256 is the Standard for Webhooks
Most webhook providers (GitHub, Stripe, Slack, etc.) use HMAC-SHA256 for these reasons:
SHA-256 is still considered cryptographically secure (as of 2026)
Good balance between security and performance
Widely supported across languages and platforms
Resistant to known attacks on older hash functions (MD5, SHA-1)
Recommendation:
HMAC-SHA256 is currently the best default choice for webhook signatures.
