Summary
HMAC-SHA256 is still secure and widely recommended for webhook signatures.
The biggest risks usually come from implementation mistakes, not the algorithm itself.
Always use constant-time comparison and verify the raw body.
Adding a timestamp significantly improves security against replay attacks.
